      'type': 'text',
      'content': '# Introduction to Electrical Systems\n\nElectricity powers our modern world! From the lights in your home to your smartphone, electrical systems are everywhere.\n\n## What is Electric Current?\n\n**Electric current** is the flow of electric charges (electrons) through a conductor.\n\n- **SI Unit**: Ampere (A)\n- **Symbol**: I\n- Measured using an **ammeter** connected in series\n\n### Analogy:\nThink of electric current like water flowing through a pipe:\n- More water flow = higher current\n- More electrons flowing = higher current\n\n## What is Voltage?\n\n**Voltage** (potential difference) is the \'push\' that makes electric charges move.\n\n- **SI Unit**: Volt (V)\n- **Symbol**: V\n- Measured using a **voltmeter** connected in parallel\n\n### Analogy:\nVoltage is like water pressure in a pipe:\n- Higher pressure = water flows faster\n- Higher voltage = electrons flow faster\n\n## What is Resistance?\n\n**Resistance** is the opposition to the flow of electric current.\n\n- **SI Unit**: Ohm (Ω)\n- **Symbol**: R\n- Different materials have different resistances\n\n### Factors Affecting Resistance:\n1. **Material**: Copper has low resistance, rubber has high resistance\n2. **Length**: Longer wire = higher resistance\n3. **Thickness**: Thinner wire = higher resistance\n4. **Temperature**: Higher temperature = higher resistance (for most metals)\n\n---\n\n### Singapore Context:\nHDB flats use 230V AC electricity. This voltage is powerful enough to run appliances but requires safety precautions!',
      'content_zh': '# 电路系统简介\n\n电力驱动着我们的现代世界！从家里的灯到智能手机，电路系统无处不在。\n\n## 什么是电流？\n\n**电流**是电荷（电子）通过导体的流动。\n\n- **国际单位**：安培 (A)\n- **符号**：I\n- 使用串联连接的**电流表**测量\n\n### 类比：\n把电流想象成水在管道中流动：\n- 水流量越大 = 电流越大\n- 流动的电子越多 = 电流越大\n\n## 什么是电压？\n\n**电压**（电位差）是推动电荷移动的'力'。\n\n- **国际单位**：伏特 (V)\n- **符号**：V\n- 使用并联连接的**电压表**测量\n\n### 类比：\n电压就像管道中的水压：\n- 压力越高 = 水流得越快\n- 电压越高 = 电子流动得越快\n\n## 什么是电阻？\n\n**电阻**是对电流流动的阻力。\n\n- **国际单位**：欧姆 (Ω)\n- **符号**：R\n- 不同材料有不同的电阻\n\n### 影响电阻的因素：\n1. **材料**：铜的电阻低，橡胶的电阻高\n2. **长度**：导线越长 = 电阻越大\n3. **粗细**：导线越细 = 电阻越大\n4. **温度**：温度越高 = 电阻越大（对于大多数金属）\n\n---\n\n### 新加坡背景：\n组屋使用230V交流电。这个电压足以运行电器，但需要采取安全预防措施！'
    },
    {
      'type': 'text',
      'content': '# Circuit Diagrams and Components\n\n## Standard Circuit Symbols\n\nElectrical circuits are represented using standard symbols:\n\n| Component | Symbol | Function |\n|-----------|--------|----------|\n| **Cell** | ─\\|\\|─ | Provides electrical energy (1.5V) |\n| **Battery** | ─\\|\\|─\\|\\|─ | Multiple cells together |\n| **Switch (Open)** | ─/ ─ | Breaks the circuit |\n| **Switch (Closed)** | ─●─ | Completes the circuit |\n| **Bulb/Lamp** | ─⊗─ | Converts electrical energy to light |\n| **Resistor** | ─▭─ | Opposes current flow |\n| **Ammeter** | ─(A)─ | Measures current (series) |\n| **Voltmeter** | ─(V)─ | Measures voltage (parallel) |\n| **Wire** | ──── | Conducts electricity |\n\n## Drawing Circuit Diagrams\n\n**Rules:**\n1. Use standard symbols\n2. Draw circuits as rectangles (not messy circles)\n3. Components should be evenly spaced\n4. Wires are represented as straight lines\n5. Ammeters go IN SERIES (same path as current)\n6. Voltmeters go IN PARALLEL (across component)\n\n### Example Circuit:\n```\nBattery → Switch → Bulb → Ammeter → back to Battery\n      ↓\n   Voltmeter across bulb\n```\n\n---\n\n### Singapore Context:\nThe circuit breaker box in your HDB flat uses switches to protect different circuits. When you trip a breaker, you're opening a switch!',
      'content_zh': '# 电路图和元件\n\n## 标准电路符号\n\n电路使用标准符号表示：\n\n| 元件 | 符号 | 功能 |\n|-----------|--------|----------|\n| **电池** | ─\\|\\|─ | 提供电能（1.5V） |\n| **电池组** | ─\\|\\|─\\|\\|─ | 多个电池组合 |\n| **开关（断开）** | ─/ ─ | 断开电路 |\n| **开关（闭合）** | ─●─ | 接通电路 |\n| **灯泡** | ─⊗─ | 将电能转换为光能 |\n| **电阻器** | ─▭─ | 阻碍电流流动 |\n| **电流表** | ─(A)─ | 测量电流（串联） |\n| **电压表** | ─(V)─ | 测量电压（并联） |\n| **导线** | ──── | 导电 |\n\n## 绘制电路图\n\n**规则：**\n1. 使用标准符号\n2. 将电路画成矩形（不要画成混乱的圆圈）\n3. 元件应均匀分布\n4. 导线用直线表示\n5. 电流表串联（与电流路径相同）\n6. 电压表并联（跨接元件）\n\n### 示例电路：\n```\n电池 → 开关 → 灯泡 → 电流表 → 返回电池\n      ↓\n   电压表跨接灯泡\n```\n\n---\n\n### 新加坡背景：\n组屋中的断路器盒使用开关来保护不同的电路。当你跳闸时，你就是在打开一个开关！'
