    {
      'type': 'text',
      'content': '# Effects of Electric Current\n\nElectric current produces three main effects:\n\n## 1. Chemical Effect\n\n**What happens?** Chemical reactions occur when electricity passes through certain liquids.\n\n### Examples:\n- **Electroplating**: Coating objects with metal (e.g., gold-plating jewelry)\n- **Electrolysis**: Breaking down compounds (e.g., splitting water into hydrogen and oxygen)\n- **Batteries**: Chemical reactions produce electricity\n\n### In Singapore:\nElectroplating factories use this effect to coat MRT train parts with protective metals!\n\n---\n\n## 2. Heating Effect\n\n**What happens?** Electric current flowing through a resistor produces heat.\n\n**Why?** Electrons collide with atoms in the wire, converting electrical energy to thermal energy.\n\n### Formula:\nHeat produced depends on:\n- **Current (I)**: Higher current = more heat\n- **Resistance (R)**: Higher resistance = more heat\n- **Time (t)**: Longer time = more heat\n\n### Examples:\n- **Electric kettle**: Heats water\n- **Toaster**: Heats bread\n- **Hair dryer**: Heats air\n- **Iron**: Heats clothes\n- **Rice cooker**: Heats rice (very common in Singapore!)\n\n### Safety Note:\nOverheating wires can cause fires! This is why we use fuses and circuit breakers.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Magnetic Effect\n\n**What happens?** A wire carrying electric current produces a magnetic field around it.\n\n### Applications:\n- **Electromagnets**: Temporary magnets (can be turned on/off)\n- **Electric bells**: Use electromagnets to create sound\n- **Motors**: Convert electrical energy to motion (in fans, washing machines)\n- **Generators**: Convert motion to electrical energy (in power stations)\n\n### In Singapore:\nMRT trains use powerful electromagnets in their motors. Some newer trains use magnetic levitation!',
      'content_zh': '# 电流的效应\n\n电流产生三种主要效应：\n\n## 1. 化学效应\n\n**发生什么？** 当电流通过某些液体时会发生化学反应。\n\n### 例子：\n- **电镀**：用金属涂覆物体（例如，镀金珠宝）\n- **电解**：分解化合物（例如，将水分解成氢气和氧气）\n- **电池**：化学反应产生电能\n\n### 在新加坡：\n电镀工厂使用这种效应为地铁列车部件涂上保护金属！\n\n---\n\n## 2. 热效应\n\n**发生什么？** 电流流过电阻器时产生热量。\n\n**为什么？** 电子与导线中的原子碰撞，将电能转换为热能。\n\n### 公式：\n产生的热量取决于：\n- **电流 (I)**：电流越大 = 热量越多\n- **电阻 (R)**：电阻越大 = 热量越多\n- **时间 (t)**：时间越长 = 热量越多\n\n### 例子：\n- **电热水壶**：加热水\n- **烤面包机**：加热面包\n- **吹风机**：加热空气\n- **熨斗**：熨烫衣服\n- **电饭煲**：煮饭（在新加坡很常见！）\n\n### 安全提示：\n导线过热会引起火灾！这就是我们使用保险丝和断路器的原因。\n\n---\n\n## 3. 磁效应\n\n**发生什么？** 载流导线周围会产生磁场。\n\n### 应用：\n- **电磁铁**：临时磁铁（可以打开/关闭）\n- **电铃**：使用电磁铁产生声音\n- **电动机**：将电能转换为运动（在风扇、洗衣机中）\n- **发电机**：将运动转换为电能（在发电厂中）\n\n### 在新加坡：\n地铁列车在其电动机中使用强大的电磁铁。一些较新的列车使用磁悬浮技术！'
    },
    {
      'type': 'text',
      'content': '# Electrical Power and Energy\n\n## What is Electrical Power?\n\n**Power** is the rate at which electrical energy is converted to other forms of energy.\n\n- **SI Unit**: Watt (W)\n- **Symbol**: P\n- **Formula**: P = VI (Power = Voltage × Current)\n\n### Common Power Ratings:\n- LED bulb: 5-10 W\n- Ceiling fan: 50-70 W\n- Laptop: 60-100 W\n- Desktop computer: 200-500 W\n- Air conditioner: 1000-2500 W (1-2.5 kW)\n- Washing machine: 500-1500 W\n\n---\n\n## Electrical Energy Consumption\n\n**Energy** is the total amount of electrical work done.\n\n- **SI Unit**: Joule (J) or kilowatt-hour (kWh)\n- **Symbol**: E\n- **Formula**: E = Pt (Energy = Power × Time)\n\n### Converting Units:\n- 1 kWh = 1000 W × 3600 s = 3,600,000 J = 3.6 MJ\n\n---\n\n## Calculating Electricity Bills (Singapore)\n\nIn Singapore, electricity is charged in **cents per kWh**.\n\n**Current rates (SP Group, 2024):**\n- ~30-40 cents per kWh (varies with tariff)\n\n### Example Calculation:\n\nYour family uses a 1.5 kW air conditioner for 8 hours per day for 30 days.\n\n**Step 1:** Calculate energy used\n- Energy = Power × Time\n- Energy = 1.5 kW × (8 hours/day × 30 days)\n- Energy = 1.5 kW × 240 hours\n- Energy = 360 kWh\n\n**Step 2:** Calculate cost\n- Cost = Energy × Rate\n- Cost = 360 kWh × $0.35/kWh\n- Cost = $126\n\n**Tip:** Using air-con wisely can save hundreds of dollars per year!\n\n---\n\n## Energy-Saving Tips (for Singapore Homes)\n\n1. **Use LED bulbs**: 80% less energy than incandescent bulbs\n2. **Set air-con to 25°C**: Each degree lower uses ~10% more energy\n3. **Turn off appliances**: Don't leave them on standby mode\n4. **Use ceiling fans**: Uses 20× less energy than air-con\n5. **Choose energy-efficient appliances**: Look for higher tick ratings\n\n**Singapore's Energy Label:**\n- 4-5 ticks = Most efficient\n- 1 tick = Least efficient',
      'content_zh': '# 电功率和电能\n\n## 什么是电功率？\n\n**功率**是电能转换为其他形式能量的速率。\n\n- **国际单位**：瓦特 (W)\n- **符号**：P\n- **公式**：P = VI（功率 = 电压 × 电流）\n\n### 常见功率额定值：\n- LED灯泡：5-10 W\n- 吊扇：50-70 W\n- 笔记本电脑：60-100 W\n- 台式电脑：200-500 W\n- 空调：1000-2500 W（1-2.5 kW）\n- 洗衣机：500-1500 W\n\n---\n\n## 电能消耗\n\n**能量**是完成的电功的总量。\n\n- **国际单位**：焦耳 (J) 或千瓦时 (kWh)\n- **符号**：E\n- **公式**：E = Pt（能量 = 功率 × 时间）\n\n### 单位转换：\n- 1 kWh = 1000 W × 3600 s = 3,600,000 J = 3.6 MJ\n\n---\n\n## 计算电费（新加坡）\n\n在新加坡，电费按**每千瓦时的分**计算。\n\n**当前费率（SP Group，2024年）：**\n- 约每千瓦时30-40分（随电价而变）\n\n### 示例计算：\n\n您家使用1.5千瓦的空调，每天开8小时，持续30天。\n\n**步骤1：** 计算使用的能量\n- 能量 = 功率 × 时间\n- 能量 = 1.5 kW × (8小时/天 × 30天)\n- 能量 = 1.5 kW × 240小时\n- 能量 = 360 kWh\n\n**步骤2：** 计算费用\n- 费用 = 能量 × 费率\n- 费用 = 360 kWh × $0.35/kWh\n- 费用 = $126\n\n**提示：** 明智地使用空调每年可以节省数百美元！\n\n---\n\n## 节能小贴士（新加坡家庭）\n\n1. **使用LED灯泡**：比白炽灯泡节能80%\n2. **将空调设置为25°C**：每降低一度会多使用约10%的能量\n3. **关闭电器**：不要让它们处于待机模式\n4. **使用吊扇**：比空调节能20倍\n5. **选择节能电器**：寻找更高的能效等级\n\n**新加坡的能源标签：**\n- 4-5个勾 = 最节能\n- 1个勾 = 最不节能'
    },
    {
      'type': 'text',
      'content': '# Electrical Safety and Hazards\n\n## Common Electrical Hazards\n\n### 1. Electric Shock\n\n**What is it?** Electric current flows through the human body.\n\n**Effects:**\n- Mild shock: Tingling sensation\n- Moderate shock: Muscle contractions, pain\n- Severe shock: Heart failure, burns, death\n\n**Danger threshold:** 230V AC (Singapore's home voltage) can be lethal!\n\n**Prevention:**\n- Never touch electrical appliances with wet hands\n- Don't use damaged plugs or sockets\n- Keep water away from electricity\n- Use insulated tools when working with electricity\n\n---\n\n### 2. Electrical Fires\n\n**Causes:**\n- Overloaded circuits (too many appliances on one socket)\n- Short circuits (damaged insulation causes direct contact)\n- Overheating wires (poor connections, old wiring)\n- Faulty appliances\n\n**Warning signs:**\n- Burning smell\n- Sparks from sockets\n- Warm plugs or switches\n- Flickering lights\n- Discolored outlets\n\n**Prevention:**\n- Don't overload power strips\n- Replace damaged cords immediately\n- Turn off appliances when not in use\n- Use appropriate fuses\n\n---\n\n### 3. Overheating Appliances\n\n**Causes:**\n- Running high-power appliances for too long\n- Poor ventilation\n- Dust buildup blocking cooling\n\n**Prevention:**\n- Give appliances breaks (especially air-con, computers)\n- Clean vents regularly\n- Don't cover appliances while in use\n\n---\n\n## Safety Devices\n\n### 1. Fuse\n\n**What is it?** A thin wire that melts when current is too high.\n\n**How it works:**\n- Normal current → Fuse remains intact\n- Excessive current → Fuse melts (breaks circuit)\n- Circuit is protected from damage\n\n**Rating:** Fuses are rated in amperes (e.g., 3A, 5A, 13A)\n\n**Important:** Always replace with same rating fuse!\n\n---\n\n### 2. Circuit Breaker\n\n**What is it?** An automatic switch that turns off when current is too high.\n\n**Advantages over fuse:**\n- Reusable (just flip switch back)\n- Faster response\n- More reliable\n\n**In Singapore homes:**\nYour HDB flat has a circuit breaker box with multiple switches for different circuits (lights, power points, air-con).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Earth Wire (Ground Wire)\n\n**What is it?** A safety wire that provides a low-resistance path to the ground.\n\n**How it works:**\n- If appliance casing becomes live (due to fault)\n- Earth wire carries current safely to ground\n- Circuit breaker trips immediately\n- You don't get shocked!\n\n**Singapore plugs:**\n- 3-pin plugs have earth wire (top pin)\n- Metal appliances (washing machines, fridges) need earth wire\n\n---\n\n### 4. Residual Current Circuit Breaker (RCCB)\n\n**What is it?** Detects tiny current leaks and cuts power instantly.\n\n**Used in:** Bathrooms and outdoor areas in Singapore homes\n\n**Protection:** Prevents electrocution from water contact\n\n---\n\n## Emergency Procedures\n\n### If someone gets electric shock:\n\n1. **DON'T touch the person directly** (you'll get shocked too!)\n2. **Turn off power** at main switch or unplug device\n3. If you can't turn off power:\n   - Use non-conductive object (dry wood, plastic) to separate person from source\n4. Call **995** (Singapore emergency number)\n5. Check breathing and pulse\n6. Perform CPR if trained\n\n### If electrical fire occurs:\n\n1. **Turn off main power** if safe to do so\n2. **DON'T use water** (electricity + water = danger!)\n3. Use **CO₂ or dry powder fire extinguisher**\n4. If fire is large, evacuate and call **995**\n5. Close doors to contain fire\n\n---\n\n## Safe Electricity Practices\n\n✅ **DO:**\n- Check cords and plugs regularly for damage\n- Turn off and unplug appliances during thunderstorms\n- Use proper outlets (3-pin for high-power devices)\n- Keep electrical items away from water\n- Replace old/damaged appliances\n- Hire licensed electricians for repairs\n\n❌ **DON'T:**\n- Yank cords out by pulling the wire\n- Overload extension cords\n- Use appliances with damaged cords\n- Touch switches with wet hands\n- Poke objects into electrical outlets\n- Attempt electrical repairs without training\n\n---\n\n### Singapore Regulations\n\n**Energy Market Authority (EMA)** regulates electrical safety:\n- All electrical products must be registered\n- Electricians must be licensed\n- Regular inspections for commercial buildings\n- Safety standards for appliances',
      'content_zh': '# 电气安全和危险\n\n## 常见电气危险\n\n### 1. 触电\n\n**什么是触电？** 电流流过人体。\n\n**影响：**\n- 轻微触电：刺痛感\n- 中度触电：肌肉收缩、疼痛\n- 严重触电：心脏衰竭、烧伤、死亡\n\n**危险阈值：** 230V交流电（新加坡家庭电压）可能致命！\n\n**预防：**\n- 切勿用湿手触摸电器\n- 不要使用损坏的插头或插座\n- 让水远离电\n- 使用绝缘工具处理电气设备\n\n---\n\n### 2. 电气火灾\n\n**原因：**\n- 电路过载（一个插座上有太多电器）\n- 短路（绝缘层损坏导致直接接触）\n- 导线过热（连接不良、旧线路）\n- 电器故障\n\n**警告信号：**\n- 烧焦的气味\n- 插座冒火花\n- 插头或开关发热\n- 灯光闪烁\n- 插座变色\n\n**预防：**\n- 不要使插线板过载\n- 立即更换损坏的电线\n- 不使用时关闭电器\n- 使用适当的保险丝\n\n---\n\n### 3. 电器过热\n\n**原因：**\n- 大功率电器运行时间过长\n- 通风不良\n- 灰尘堆积阻碍散热\n\n**预防：**\n- 让电器休息（特别是空调、电脑）\n- 定期清洁通风口\n- 使用时不要覆盖电器\n\n---\n\n## 安全装置\n\n### 1. 保险丝\n\n**什么是保险丝？** 当电流过大时会熔断的细导线。\n\n**工作原理：**\n- 正常电流 → 保险丝保持完好\n- 过大电流 → 保险丝熔断（断开电路）\n- 电路受到保护\n\n**额定值：** 保险丝以安培为单位（例如，3A、5A、13A）\n\n**重要：** 始终用相同额定值的保险丝更换！\n\n---\n\n### 2. 断路器\n\n**什么是断路器？** 当电流过大时自动关闭的开关。\n\n**比保险丝的优势：**\n- 可重复使用（只需翻回开关）\n- 响应更快\n- 更可靠\n\n**在新加坡家庭：**\n组屋有一个断路器盒，有多个开关用于不同的电路（灯、电源插座、空调）。\n\n---\n\n### 3. 接地线（地线）\n\n**什么是接地线？** 提供通往地面的低电阻路径的安全线。\n\n**工作原理：**\n- 如果电器外壳带电（由于故障）\n- 接地线将电流安全地引导到地面\n- 断路器立即跳闸\n- 你不会触电！\n\n**新加坡插头：**\n- 三脚插头有接地线（顶部插脚）\n- 金属电器（洗衣机、冰箱）需要接地线\n\n---\n\n### 4. 漏电断路器 (RCCB)\n\n**什么是漏电断路器？** 检测微小的电流泄漏并立即切断电源。\n\n**用于：** 新加坡家庭的浴室和室外区域\n\n**保护：** 防止因接触水而触电\n\n---\n\n## 应急程序\n\n### 如果有人触电：\n\n1. **不要直接触摸该人**（你也会触电！）\n2. **关闭电源**在主开关处或拔掉设备插头\n3. 如果无法关闭电源：\n   - 使用非导电物体（干木头、塑料）将人与电源分离\n4. 拨打**995**（新加坡紧急电话）\n5. 检查呼吸和脉搏\n6. 如果受过训练，进行心肺复苏\n\n### 如果发生电气火灾：\n\n1. **关闭主电源**如果安全的话\n2. **不要使用水**（电 + 水 = 危险！）\n3. 使用**CO₂或干粉灭火器**\n4. 如果火灾很大，撤离并拨打**995**\n5. 关闭门以控制火势\n\n---\n\n## 安全用电实践\n\n✅ **应该：**\n- 定期检查电线和插头是否损坏\n- 雷暴期间关闭并拔掉电器插头\n- 使用适当的插座（大功率设备使用三脚插头）\n- 让电器远离水\n- 更换旧的/损坏的电器\n- 聘请持照电工进行维修\n\n❌ **不应该：**\n- 拉扯电线拔出插头\n- 使延长线过载\n- 使用有损坏电线的电器\n- 用湿手触摸开关\n- 将物体插入电源插座\n- 未经培训尝试电气维修\n\n---\n\n### 新加坡法规\n\n**能源市场管理局 (EMA)** 监管电气安全：\n- 所有电气产品必须注册\n- 电工必须持照\n- 商业建筑的定期检查\n- 电器的安全标准'
