    {
      'type': 'text',
      'content': '# Series and Parallel Circuits (G3)\n\nNote: This section is **optional for G2** students but required for G3.\n\n---\n\n## Series Circuits\n\n**Definition:** Components connected one after another in a single path.\n\n### Characteristics:\n\n**Current:**\n- Same current flows through all components\n- I₁ = I₂ = I₃\n- If one component fails, entire circuit stops\n\n**Voltage:**\n- Total voltage splits among components\n- V_total = V₁ + V₂ + V₃\n- Components with higher resistance get more voltage\n\n**Resistance:**\n- Total resistance = sum of all resistances\n- R_total = R₁ + R₂ + R₃\n- Adding resistors increases total resistance\n\n### Advantages:\n- Simple design\n- Uses less wire\n\n### Disadvantages:\n- If one component breaks, all stop working\n- Bulbs become dimmer as you add more\n- Not practical for home wiring\n\n### Real-world example:\n- Decorative Christmas lights (old style)\n- If one bulb burns out, all lights go out!\n\n---\n\n## Parallel Circuits\n\n**Definition:** Components connected across common points with multiple paths.\n\n### Characteristics:\n\n**Current:**\n- Total current splits among branches\n- I_total = I₁ + I₂ + I₃\n- Each branch can work independently\n\n**Voltage:**\n- Same voltage across all components\n- V₁ = V₂ = V₃ = V_total\n\n**Resistance:**\n- Total resistance is LESS than smallest individual resistance\n- 1/R_total = 1/R₁ + 1/R₂ + 1/R₃\n- Adding resistors decreases total resistance\n\n### Advantages:\n- If one component fails, others keep working\n- All components get full voltage (bulbs stay bright)\n- Can control each component separately with switches\n- Practical for home wiring\n\n### Disadvantages:\n- Uses more wire\n- More complex design\n\n### Real-world example:\n- **HDB electrical system**: All your home appliances are in parallel\n  - You can turn off one light without affecting others\n  - TV works even if fridge is unplugged\n  - Each room can have separate switch\n\n---\n\n## Comparison Table\n\n| Feature | Series | Parallel |\n|---------|--------|----------|\n| **Current** | Same everywhere | Splits among branches |\n| **Voltage** | Splits among components | Same everywhere |\n| **Resistance** | R_total = R₁ + R₂ + R₃ | 1/R_total = 1/R₁ + 1/R₂ + 1/R₃ |\n| **One component fails** | All stop | Others continue |\n| **Brightness (bulbs)** | Dimmer with more bulbs | Same brightness |\n| **Common use** | Simple devices | Home wiring |\n\n---\n\n## Why are homes wired in parallel?\n\n**Singapore HDB flats** use parallel circuits because:\n\n1. **Independence**: Can use air-con without turning on lights\n2. **Consistent voltage**: All appliances get full 230V\n3. **Safety**: Faulty appliance doesn't cut power to entire flat\n4. **Convenience**: Individual switches for each appliance\n5. **Circuit breaker protection**: Each circuit can have separate breaker\n\n**Fun fact:** Your flat might have 5-8 separate parallel circuits:\n- Living room lights\n- Bedroom lights\n- Living room power points\n- Bedroom power points\n- Kitchen\n- Air-conditioners\n- Water heater\n- Stove (electric)',
      'content_zh': '# 串联和并联电路（G3）\n\n注意：此部分对**G2学生是可选的**，但对G3学生是必需的。\n\n---\n\n## 串联电路\n\n**定义：** 元件在单一路径中依次连接。\n\n### 特征：\n\n**电流：**\n- 相同的电流流过所有元件\n- I₁ = I₂ = I₃\n- 如果一个元件失效，整个电路停止工作\n\n**电压：**\n- 总电压在元件之间分配\n- V_总 = V₁ + V₂ + V₃\n- 电阻更高的元件获得更多电压\n\n**电阻：**\n- 总电阻 = 所有电阻之和\n- R_总 = R₁ + R₂ + R₃\n- 添加电阻器会增加总电阻\n\n### 优点：\n- 设计简单\n- 使用较少的导线\n\n### 缺点：\n- 如果一个元件损坏，所有元件都停止工作\n- 添加更多灯泡会变暗\n- 不适合家庭布线\n\n### 现实世界的例子：\n- 装饰性圣诞灯（旧式）\n- 如果一个灯泡烧坏，所有灯都会熄灭！\n\n---\n\n## 并联电路\n\n**定义：** 元件跨公共点连接，有多条路径。\n\n### 特征：\n\n**电流：**\n- 总电流在分支之间分配\n- I_总 = I₁ + I₂ + I₃\n- 每个分支可以独立工作\n\n**电压：**\n- 所有元件上的电压相同\n- V₁ = V₂ = V₃ = V_总\n\n**电阻：**\n- 总电阻小于最小的单个电阻\n- 1/R_总 = 1/R₁ + 1/R₂ + 1/R₃\n- 添加电阻器会降低总电阻\n\n### 优点：\n- 如果一个元件失效，其他元件继续工作\n- 所有元件获得全电压（灯泡保持明亮）\n- 可以用开关单独控制每个元件\n- 适合家庭布线\n\n### 缺点：\n- 使用更多导线\n- 设计更复杂\n\n### 现实世界的例子：\n- **组屋电气系统**：所有家用电器都是并联的\n  - 可以关闭一盏灯而不影响其他灯\n  - 即使拔掉冰箱插头，电视也能工作\n  - 每个房间可以有单独的开关\n\n---\n\n## 比较表\n\n| 特征 | 串联 | 并联 |\n|---------|--------|----------|\n| **电流** | 处处相同 | 在分支之间分配 |\n| **电压** | 在元件之间分配 | 处处相同 |\n| **电阻** | R_总 = R₁ + R₂ + R₃ | 1/R_总 = 1/R₁ + 1/R₂ + 1/R₃ |\n| **一个元件失效** | 全部停止 | 其他继续 |\n| **亮度（灯泡）** | 灯泡越多越暗 | 亮度相同 |\n| **常见用途** | 简单设备 | 家庭布线 |\n\n---\n\n## 为什么家庭使用并联布线？\n\n**新加坡组屋**使用并联电路因为：\n\n1. **独立性**：可以在不开灯的情况下使用空调\n2. **电压一致**：所有电器都获得完整的230V\n3. **安全**：故障电器不会切断整个公寓的电源\n4. **便利**：每个电器都有单独的开关\n5. **断路器保护**：每个电路可以有单独的断路器\n\n**有趣的事实：** 您的公寓可能有5-8个单独的并联电路：\n- 客厅灯\n- 卧室灯\n- 客厅电源插座\n- 卧室电源插座\n- 厨房\n- 空调\n- 热水器\n- 炉灶（电）'
